  "market_context": "Intraday consolidation after an initial rise from 68.00 to 68.55 (03:00–04:30). Price formed a tight range between ~68.20–68.50, with London session consolidation and a subsequent manipulation of the lower boundary.",
  "key_observation": "Price swept the consolidation low (turtle soup), then closed back above the fair value gap that formed the down leg (inversion), followed by a close through the down-close candle (change in state of delivery), confirming a bullish reversal toward the upper range boundary.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified a consolidation range between ~68.20 and 68.50 on the 3M CL1! chart, noting failure to displace either side initially.",
    "Step 2: Observed price sweeping the lower boundary of the range (turtle soup/purge of low) around 05:06, signaling potential manipulation.",
    "Step 3: Noted a close above the fair value gap created by the down move (inversion), providing increased confirmation of reversal.",
    "Step 4: Identified a change in state of delivery as price closed above the single down-close candle that formed the low, forming a valid order block.",
    "Step 5: Confirmed further structure with a fair value gap and breaker block formation (low-high-lower low-higher high sequence) before expansion toward the upper range boundary at ~68.50."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price retraced into the FVG zone, found support, and expanded higher through the upper range boundary (~68.50), achieving the target side of the consolidation range.",
  "lessons": "Reversals in consolidation ranges follow a hierarchy of confirmation: turtle soup (lowest) → inversion → change in state of delivery → FVG/breaker block (highest). Entering earlier sacrifices confirmation but offers better risk-reward; simplifying to one PD array improves clarity.",
